Furthermore, the high level of reactive oxygen complexes (reactive oxygen complexes) arising from the high metabolic activity of bats can both suppress the transcription of the coronavirus and influence the correction by external ribonuclease, thus providing selective pressure for highly pathogenic strains of the virus to emerge when a new host is infected.
