Although questions are still on the table, there is no evidence that SARS-CoV-2 is man-made, either intentionally or by accident.
Coronaviruses have returned to the spotlight because of the recent SARS-CoV-2 outbreak.
The study of coronaviruses in bats and other animals has dramatically changed our idea of the importance of the origins of animal diseases and animal repositories of human coronaviruses in human transmission.
Crucial evidence has shown that SARS-CoV, MERS-CoV, and SARS-CoV-2 all originated from bats and were transmitted to humans via intermediate flight attendants.
Based on the fact that SARS-CoV infection arose from the contact between humans and yogurt cats in the markets, the closure of the fresh produce markets and the killing of yogurt cats were supposed to effectively end the SARS epidemic.
